cs.MA, cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the management of large EV fleets through self-interested EV aggregators who compete in a market. 
- cs.GT (Game Theory) is also likely as the paper studies the strategic manipulation of the ADMM algorithm by the self-interested aggregators. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes a decentralised algorithm employing the Alternating Direction Method of Multipliers (ADMM) and a detection algorithm to detect manipulation. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with the coordination of EV charging and the impact on electricity markets. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is relevant as the paper proposes a mathematical framework to quantify and detect manipulation, which is important for ensuring the security and privacy of the system.
